io.github.zachohara.bukkit.simpleplugin.command

Class Properties

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.github.zachohara.bukkit.simpleplugin.command.Properties

  • public class Properties
extends java.lang.Object
    A Properties object is specific to a single command. It should contain information about the expected context of a command, such as the allowed amount of arguments, and the required permission level of the sender. A Properties object is also responsible for verifying the conditions of any given command.
    Author:
    Zach Ohara

      • verifyCommand

        public boolean verifyCommand(CommandInstance command)
        Checks the validity of the conditions that this command was sent with. The method will verify the following things about the conditions of the command:
        1. An appropriate number of arguments were sent with the command.
        2. The target player that was specified with the command (if applicable) is a valid player given the conditions of the specific command.
        3. The entity that sent the command has permission to use the specific command.
        If all the above conditions are met given the circumstances, the command has been successfully verified, and this method will return true.
        Parameters:
        command - the CommandInstance that should be check against this set of properties.
        Returns:
        true if and only if all prerequisite conditions for the command are met; false otherwise.
        See Also:
        verifyValidArguments(CommandInstance), verifyValidTarget(CommandInstance), verifyValidSource(CommandInstance)

      • verifyValidArguments

        private boolean verifyValidArguments(CommandInstance command)
        Verifies that the given command was sent with an appropriate amount of arguments. If the amount of arguments is not valid, this method will return an appropriate response to the player or console that sent the command.
        Parameters:
        command - the CommandInstance that should be check against this set of properties.
        Returns:
        true if and only if the amount of arguments that were sent with the command match the expected conditions for the command; false otherwise.
        See Also:
        verifyCommand(CommandInstance)

      • verifyValidTarget

        private boolean verifyValidTarget(CommandInstance command)
        Verifies that the specified target player is a valid target player that is not specially protected from this command. If the specified target player is not valid, this method will return an appropriate response to the player or console that sent the command.
        Parameters:
        command - the CommandInstance that should be check against this set of properties.
        Returns:
        true if and only if the specified target player is a valid target for this command; false otherwise.
        See Also:
        verifyCommand(CommandInstance)

      • verifyValidSource

        private boolean verifyValidSource(CommandInstance command)
        Verifies that the entity that sent this command has permission to do so. If the sender does not have the required permission to use this command, this method will return an appropriate response to the player or console that sent this command.
        Parameters:
        command - the CommandInstance that should be check against this set of properties.
        Returns:
        true if and only if the entity that sent this command has the required permission and ability to do so; false otherwise.
        See Also:
        verifyCommand(CommandInstance)
